<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idbf4256df-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa" identifier="/us/usc/t42/s11344"><num value="11344">§ 11344.</num><heading> Limitation on certain costs</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Not more than 5 percent of the total amount appropriated for the emergency food and shelter program for each fiscal year may be expended for the costs of administration.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idbf4256e0-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa">(<ref href="/us/pl/100/77/tIII/s314">Pub. L. 100–77, title III, § 314</ref>, <date date="1987-07-22">July 22, 1987</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/101/492">101 Stat. 492</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
